cunning as a Maori dog
Homonym Number:
Word Class:phrase
Sense Number:
Definition:(of a person or animal) extremely perceptive and/or manipulative.
Origin:[none]
Register:
Register 2:
Domain:[none]
Region:[none]
See:
Pronunciation:
Notes: ca1890 at least R. Mason's mother remembered it from c1890 in the Wanganui-Bulls district.
